articles.author: Jonathan Landay
articles.description: One expert said the strikes may have hampered Iran's ability to mass-produce missiles.
articles.title: Exclusive: Satellite photos show Israel hit Iran missile fuel-mixing facilities, researchers say

articles.author: Parisa Hafezi, Emily Rose
articles.description: Israel hit back at Iran early on Saturday, with its military saying it was conducting strikes against military targets in response to Tehran's attacks on Israel.
articles.title: Israel hits back at Iran with strikes on military targets, IDF says

articles.author: Sakura Murakami
articles.description: Political wrangling could roil markets and be a headache for the Bank of Japan.
articles.title: Japan votes in election expected to punish PM Ishiba's coalition

articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi
articles.description: Israeli forces withdrew from a hospital complex in northern Gaza on Saturday, one day after storming it, and the Palestinian enclave's health ministry said the troops had detained dozens of male medical staffers and some of the patients.
articles.title: Israeli army leaves north Gaza hospital, detains medics, says health ministry

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Russian forces have advanced further into several eastern Ukrainian towns, bringing them closer to capturing the strategic city of Pokrovsk, Russian and Ukrainian bloggers said.
articles.title: Russian forces advance toward Ukraine's strategic Pokrovsk, military bloggers say

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: China will take "countermeasures" to defend its sovereignty and territorial integrity, the government said, lambasting a $2 billion arms sale package by the United States to Taiwan.
articles.title: China vows 'countermeasures' after $2 bln US arms sale to Taiwan

articles.author: Felix Light, Lucy Papachristou
articles.description: Georgians vote on Saturday in a parliamentary election depicted by both sides as an existential battle that will determine whether the country integrates closely with the West or leans back towards Moscow.
articles.title: Georgia votes in election seen as stark choice between Russia and West

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Bulgarians head to the polls on Sunday for their seventh snap election in four years but opinion surveys suggest it is unlikely to break a political deadlock that has slowed economic reforms in the European Union's poorest member state.
articles.title: Bulgaria holds another snap election, no stable government in sight

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Storm Trami is making landfall in central Vietnam on Sunday as the authorities warn the heavy rains it triggers could cause dangerous floods.
articles.title: Storm Trami lands in central Vietnam posing flood risks

articles.author: Andrius Sytas
articles.description: Lithuanians head to the polls on Sunday to decide a parliamentary election dominated by concerns over the cost of living and potential threats from neighbouring Russia, with the opposition Social Democrats ahead after the first-round vote.
articles.title: Lithuania opposition seeks to cement election win in run-off votes
